  <ac:layout-section ac:type=\"single\">
    <ac:layout-cell>
      <p>Requirements stage. Gate R is a conclusion of the requirements management. The main idea of this gate is to make sure that the product requirements are compiled in PRS and verified in ATS, in a way that is understandable to the customer. Additionally, it's necessary is to have customer's approval of the PRS and ATS at this stage.</p>
      <p>Points from the checklist can be skipped/waived if it is judged to fit the project better. However, the decision about waiving points of the checklist shall be made and agreed with the CTO <u>
          <strong>and</strong>
        </u> PD in time, before the gate meeting is conducted. The argument for waiving a point shall be stated inside the checklist along with the date of agreement and initials of the responsible.</p>
      <br/>
      <p>See a further description of each point here: <span style=\"color: rgb(255,0,0);\">
          <a href=\"https://<CONFLUENCE_HOST>/display/PMO/Gate+R+Description\">Gate R Description</a>
        </span>
      </p>
    </ac:layout-cell>
  </ac:layout-section>
